equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
This method first checks to see if the object in question is null and if so returns false. It then test to see if the objects refer to the same object and returns true if they do. It then checks to see if obj is an instance of Addresses and returns false if it is not or if so it then cast the object to an Addresses object and test the hashCode of each object and returns true or false depending on if the hashCodes are equals or not.
